ine.com/airframes/flynas-takes-delivery-first-a330|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140401204224/http://atwonline.com/airframes/flynas-takes-delivery-first-a330|archivedate= 1 April 2014 }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Flynas touches down in Cairo with daily non-stop flights\">{{cite news|title= Flynas touches down in Cairo with daily non-stop flights|work= [[Al Bawaba]]|date= 3 June 2014|url= http://www.albawaba.com/business/pr/flynas-cairo-non-stop-flights-580698|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140609203807/http://www.albawaba.com/business/pr/flynas-cairo-non-stop-flights-580698|archivedate= 9 June 2014 }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Inaugural Flynas flight touches down at Manchester\">{{cite news|title= Inaugural Flynas flight touches down at Manchester|work= Arabian Aerospace|date= 7 May 2014|url= http://www.arabianaerospace.aero/inaugural-flynas-flight-touches-down-at-manchester.html|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140509113956/http://www.arabianaerospace.aero/inaugural-flynas-flight-touches-down-at-manchester.html|archivedate= 9 May 2014 }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Middle Eastern carriers drop routes\">{{cite news|title= Middle Eastern carriers drop routes|first= Alan|last= Dron|work= [[Air Transport World]]|date= 28 July 2014|url= http://atwonline.com/airports-routes/middle-eastern-carriers-drop-routes|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140729111114/http://atwonline.com/airports-routes/middle-eastern-carriers-drop-routes|archivedate= 29 July 2014|df= dmy-all}}&nbsp;</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Nasair launches new routes\">{{cite news|title= Nasair launches new routes|first= Martin|last= Morris|work= arabianbusiness.com|date= 4 July 2009|url= http://www.arabianbusiness.com/nasair-launches-new-routes-16358.html|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140703200933/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/nasair-launches-new-routes-16358.html|archivedate= 3 July 2014 }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Nigerian Pilgrims in High Spirit, Commend Officials for Improved Services\">{{cite news|title= Nigerian Pilgrims in High Spirit, Commend Officials for Improved Services|first= Kabir Alabi|last= Garba|location= [[Madinah]]|agency= [[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]]|work= [[AllAfrica.com]]|date= 29 September 2014|url= http://allafrica.com/stories/201409300402.html|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141015112924/http://allafrica.com/stories/201409300402.html|archivedate= 15 October 2014|df= dmy-all}}&nbsp;</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Rebranded Nasair aiming for 20m passengers by 2020\">{{cite news|title= Rebranded Nasair aiming for 20m passengers by 2020|first= Daniel|last= Shane|work= arabianbusiness.com|date= 14 November 2014|url= http://www.arabianbusiness.com/rebranded-nasair-aiming-for-20m-passengers-by-2020-526373.html|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140703194955/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/rebranded-nasair-aiming-for-20m-passengers-by-2020-526373.html|archivedate= 3 July 2014 }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"ROUTES: Flynas to start US flights in 2015\">{{cite news|title= ROUTES: Flynas to start US flights in 2015|work= [[Flightglobal]]|date= 7 April 2014|url= http://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/routes-flynas-to-start-us-flights-in-2015-397891/|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140609210220/http://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/routes-flynas-to-start-us-flights-in-2015-397891/|archivedate= 9 June 2014 }}</ref>\n<!-- + -->\n<ref name=\"Saudia Arabian flight touches down in Manchester for first time\">{{cite news|title= Saudia Arabian flight touches down in Manchester for first time|first= Charlotte|last= Cox|newspaper= Manchester Evening News|date= 9 May 2014|url= http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/saudia-arabian-airline-flynas-touched-7095578|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140509112816/http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/saudia-a